The paper deals with the representation of graphs using boxes in 2.5 dimensions, which is a topic related to computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also involves combinatorial aspects such as graph theory and pathwidth, which suggest that it could also belong to the discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and data structures (cs.DS) categories. The study of visibility representations and grid box representations also involves graph drawing and visualization, which could place the paper in the graph theory (cs.GR) and computational complexity (cs.CC) categories.
